Description:
iamf-tools is a library for working with Immersive Audio Model and Formats (IAMF).
It provides a C++ API for reading, writing, and decoding IAMF content.
This package contains a software decoder to decode and render IAMF audio streams.

Security Considerations:
The library parses untrusted audio streams (IAMF files and packets) from the internet. Because it is written in C++, memory safety is a concern. To mitigate risks:
- The library is designed to run in sandboxed utility processes within Chromium (such as the audio service or a utility decoding process).
- We have integrated fuzzing coverage under `test("iamf_tools_lib_fuzz_tests")` which leverages FuzzTest, and these fuzzers will run continuously on ClusterFuzz to find parsing vulnerabilities.

Local Modifications:
We have stripped unnecessary error strings in non-debug builds to minimize binary size footprint.

Only part of the upstream code is copied to src, see update.py.
